De Lille set the record straight and said that the budget, which proposes a 26.9% water and sanitation tariff increase and staff salary increases of 7.1%, was proposed by various line departments. She called for mayco members to be honest about their participation. READ MORE: #DeLille ready to fight as vote of no confidence succeeds “It’s not the mayor or De Lille’s draft budget, as some have tried to term it. I do not set the tariffs. “These come from relevant line departments and are supported by mayco members. “The mayco members sitting in chambers must be honest and acknowledge that they were part of these meetings. “They have oversight over the directorates and budget process so its wrong to call this the mayor’s draft budget alone,” De Lille said. @IAmAthinaMay  athina.may@inl.co.za  Cape Argus